<HEADLINE> No winner, jackpot increases to $41 million for Friday drawing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ATLANTA (AP) - The jackpot in the multistate Big Game lottery
drawing has grown to $41 million.
</P>
<P>
   None of the tickets sold for Tuesday's $35 million drawing
matched all five lotto numbers and the Big Money Ball. The next
drawing will be Friday, Sept. 1.
</P>
<P>
   Seven second-prize winners won $150,000 in Tuesday night's
drawing. Twenty four players matched four of the five lotto
numbers, plus the Big Money Ball number. Those tickets are each
worth $5,000.
</P>
<P>
   The winning numbers from Tuesday's drawing were: 4-17-31-37-47
(four, seventeen, thirty-one, thirty-seven, forty-seven). The Big
Money Ball was 9 (nine).
