   LEEZA: With her syndicated talk show now history, Leeza Gibbons
enters the next stage of her television career. She'll debut next
Tuesday as an anchor on the magazine show, ''Extra.'' It's familiar
turf for Gibbons, who spent more than a decade as a reporter and
anchor on ''Entertainment Tonight'' before going it alone.
Telepictures, the production company behind ''Extra,'' has also
hired Lisa Gregorisch-Dempsey as a new executive to oversee the
program, which starts its seventh season next week.
</P>
