<HEADLINE> Stocks Slip in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are lower in early trading. The Dow
Jones industrial average is down 35 points in today's early going.
Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold an 8-7 lead over
gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is down ten points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two and a half.
</P>
<P>
   There's news striking close to home on Wall Street. The
Zurich-based Credit Suisse Group is buying Wall Street's Donaldson,
Lufkin and Jenrette for $11.5 billion. It marks the second time
this summer that a Swiss firm has swooped in on a New York firm.
The other was the UBS purchase of PaineWebber.
</P>
<P>
   An earnings warning from Whirlpool may cause some pain for those
holding that stock. The appliance maker says it will suffer through
year-end because of Circuit City's decision to stop selling
appliances.
</P>
<P>
   The key economic item of the day looms in the coming hour. That
is the Leading Economic Indicators from the Conference Board.
</P>
