   THE TAILOR OF PANAMA: John Boorman adapts John Le Carre's spy
novel about a tailor (Geoffrey Rush) who becomes target for a
vicious spy (Pierce Brosnan).
</P>
<P>
   13 DAYS: Kevin Costner plays a presidential aide during the
Cuban missile crisis in 1962.
</P>
<P>
   TRAFFIC: Michael Douglas and Catherine Zeta-Jones head a
mega-cast in Steven Soderbergh's examination of drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
   VATEL: A love triangle in 17th-century France involving the
king, a beautiful woman and a lowly steward. Stars Gerard
Depardieu, Uma Thurman, Tim Roth.
</P>
<P>
   VERTICAL LIMIT: Chris O'Donnell heads a hazardous mission to
rescue his sister and her mountaineering team on K-2, the world's
second-tallest peak.
</P>
<P>
   WES CRAVEN PRESENTS: DRACULA 2000: The vampire goes modern Goth.
Featuring Gerard Butler, Jonny Lee Miller, Christopher Plummer.
</P>
<P>
   WHAT WOMEN WANT: An accident leaves an ad exec (Mel Gibson) able
to read women's minds, a skill he uses on his new boss (Helen
Hunt).
</P>
<P>
   UNSCHEDULED
</P>
<P>
   ALL THE PRETTY HORSES: Matt Damon stars in the romantic
adventure based on Cormac McCarthy's best seller. Billy Bob
Thornton directs.
</P>
<P>
   POLLOCK: Ed Harris plays abstract painter Jackson Pollock. With
Marcia Gay Hayden, Val Kilmer, Amy Madigan, Jeffrey Tambor. Harris
directed.
</P>
