<HEADLINE> Driver killed when vehicle crashes into parked bus  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SADDLE BROOK, N.J. (AP) - An elderly man was killed Wednesday
when his car slammed into the back of a bus that was taking on
passengers at a Route 46 bus stop.
</P>
<P>
   NJ Transit spokesman Ken Miller said the victim, whose name was
not immediately available, drove into the back of a bus on the No.
161 line between Paterson and New York shortly before noon.
</P>
<P>
   The bus was facing east on Route 46 and had stopped at a bus
stop when the accident occurred, he said. The car also was
traveling east on Route 46.
</P>
<P>
   Five of the 12 passengers aboard the bus, plus the bus driver,
complained of minor neck and back injuries and were taken to a
local hospital for treatment, Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   The driver of the car was pronounced dead at the scene.
</P>
</TEXT>
