<HEADLINE> Clinton and Lazio roll out big guns in New York Senate race  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - Senate candidates Hillary Rodham Clinton and
Rep. Rick Lazio rolled out the big guns Wednesday, with the first
lady releasing a fund-raising letter from President Clinton and the
congressman running a TV ad starring John McCain.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have worked as hard as I could to turn our country around,''
the president writes in the appeal. ''Now, the work must be carried
on by others. No one is more qualified than Hillary to do it.''
</P>
<P>
   In the new Lazio ad, McCain casts doubt on Clinton's claim that
she is willing to give up unlimited soft-money campaign
contributions if her Republican opponent does the same.
</P>
