<HEADLINE> Long Island man pleads guilty in parents' slayings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   KINGSTON, N.Y. (AP) - A Long Island man pleaded guilty to
first-degree murder and arson Wednesday, admitting that he killed
his parents and burned down their vacation home.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Roberts, 23, entered his plea in Ulster County Court.
District Attorney Donald Williams Jr. said he accepted the plea
because it was the top count in the indictment. Williams said he
did not make any sentencing agreement in accepting the plea.
</P>
<P>
   The charred bodies of Seth and Ronna Roberts, who were
immigration attorneys from Great Neck, Long Island, were found in
the rubble of their Woodstock vacation home after it was torched
last Nov. 17.
</P>
<P>
   Their son, a former Syracuse University student, was accused of
killing the couple and setting their home ablaze.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis Fidler, Roberts's uncle, said Seth and Ronna Roberts took
their son to their Woodstock home to kick a heroin addiction cold
turkey. Fidler said Roberts snapped and killed his parents two days
after arriving in Woodstock.
</P>
<P>
   Sentencing was set for Oct. 6. Roberts could receive a prison
term of up to 25 years to life.
</P>
</TEXT>
