<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-30 16:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Congressional candidate caught in nasty divorce spat  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Congressional candidate Larry Seabrook is
embroiled in a bitter divorce flap with his ex-wife, who claims he
divorced her without her knowing it, according to a newspaper
report Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   In sealed court papers obtained by the New York Daily News,
LaVerne Seabrook said while she was in the dark about the 1993
divorce she and Larry Seabrook continued signing joint tax returns
and he got her to co-sign a $140,000 bank equity loan, the Daily
News reported. LaVerne Seabrook claimed she did not know about the
divorce until last year.
</P>
<P>
   Seabrook, a Democratic state senator from the Bronx, denied that
his ex-wife was unaware of the split. But he refused to discuss the
divorce, saying he was barred from doing so by a court order.
</P>
<P>
   Seabrook, 49, is locked in a tight primary battle with six-term
incumbent Rep. Eliot Engel in the New York Democratic Primary Sept.
12. Engel's district covers the north Bronx and southern
Westchester County.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday Seabrook lashed out at Engel accusing the
congressman of attempting ''a public lynching of an opponent.''
</P>
<P>
   The Engel camp has denied leaking the documents.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, LaVerne Seabrook issued a statement through her
ex-husband's campaign saying she did not provide the documents to
the Daily News and said the story was painful for the couple's
children
</P>
<P>
   ''I am a private person and wish to remain so,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   She could not be reached for additional comment.
</P>
<P>
   According to the Daily News, LaVerne Seabrook claimed in court
documents that during the years she believed they were still
married she and Larry Seabrook appeared together as husband and
wife at various political events - including a visit to the White
House.
</P>
<P>
   LaVerne Seabrook acknowledged receiving the initial divorce
summons in 1990 but said she ignored it because she believed her
marital problems would blow over, the News reported. She said her
husband never again brought up his intention to divorce her and
they continued living together until 1996.
</P>
<P>
   Seabrook's lawyer said in the court documents that he never
served LaVerne Seabrook with a copy of the final 1993 divorce
decree. The divorce was granted by default, according to the News.
</P>
<P>
   Seabrook's accountant wrote a letter stating that, except for
one year, she filed joint tax returns for the Seabrooks from 1989
through 1996, the Daily News reported.
</P>
<P>
   Seabrook campaign spokeswoman Danica Gallagher said Wednesday
that tax joint returns and the equity loan the LaVerne Seabrook
co-signed for occurred the year the couple was in the midst of the
divorce.
</P>
<P>
   According to the Internal Revenue Service, a person who
knowingly files a joint tax return when no longer married could be
guilty of filing a false statement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
