<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
DLJ, up $6.13 at $88.38
Axa, down $6.06 at $72.94
</P>
<P>
   Brokerage Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette, which is controlled by
French insurance giant Axa, agreed to be acquired by Credit Suisse
Group.
</P>
<P>
Whirlpool, unchanged at $37.88
</P>
<P>
   Prudential downgrages the stock to ''sell'' after the appliance
maker warns that earnings would be hurt by Circuit City Stores'
decision to stop selling appliances.
</P>
<P>
Sony, down $5.38 at $110.13
</P>
<P>
   Sony announces plans to spend nearly $1 billion on a new
semiconductor plant to increase the development of small-sized
liquid crystal displays.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Amazon.com, up $3.31 at $42.94
</P>
<P>
   Goldman Sachs issued a positive research report on the leading
online retailer. The stock had hit a 52-week low of $27.88 on July
31 shortly after missing second quarter revenue forecasts.
</P>
<P>
VA Linux Systems, up $6.88 at $51.81
</P>
<P>
   The company, which makes computer servers that run on the Linux
operating system, announced the availability of a new database
server.
</P>
<P>
Rambus, down $4.44 at $76.19
</P>
<P>
   Micron Technology filed a lawsuit against Rambus accusing the
semiconductor technology company of seeking to gain a monopoly on
high-speed memory technology. Micron also claimed that Rambus'
patents were invalid. Rambus denied the allegations.
</P>
<P>
Juniper Networks, up $7.75 at $203.88
</P>
<P>
   The maker of Internet routers will become a component of the
Nasdaq 100 Index starting Sept. 7, replacing Visx Inc.
</P>
</TEXT>
