<HEADLINE> Rangers Sign Derek Armstrong  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Rangers signed forward Derek
Armstrong on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The 27-year-old center scored 28 goals and added a career-high
54 assists in 77 games last season with Hartford of the American
Hockey League.
</P>
<P>
   His 82 points, also a career high, led the team and tied for the
third most in the AHL. Armstrong had seven goals and a team-high 16
assists in the postseason to win the playoff MVP award and lead
Hartford to the AHL championship.
</P>
<P>
   Armstrong, who was drafted in the sixth round of the 1992 draft
by the New York Islanders, also played for the Rangers on March 23
against Washington.
</P>
<P>
   He has nine goals and 10 assists in 83 career NHL games with the
Rangers, Islanders and Ottawa Senators.
</P>
<P>
   Armstrong tallied 124 goals and set up 212 others in 403 games
the last seven seasons with Denver, Detroit, Salt Lake and Utah of
the International Hockey League and Hartford and Worcester in the
AHL.
</P>
</TEXT>
