<HEADLINE> Pa. firm recalls franks after metal fragments found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WASHINGTON (AP) - A Pennsylvania meat processor is voluntarily
recalling 6,588 pounds of cheese franks that may be contaminated
with metal fragments.
</P>
<P>
   The franks, which were produced by Berks Packing Co. of Reading,
Pa., were distributed to grocery stores in Maryland, New Jersey,
New York, Pennsylvania and West Virginia, the Agriculture
Department said.
</P>
<P>
   The product being recalled is in one-pound packages of ''WEIS
Quality'' brand franks. Each package bears ''EST. 8782'' in the
USDA seal of inspection, and a code of ''4 Sell by Oct. 17.'' The
problem was identified after a consumer found metal fragments in
the product.
</P>
</TEXT>
