despite the flat refusal by Iraqi authorities to allow inspectors in the
country. Hans Blix, executive chairman of the U.N. Monitoring, Verification and
Inspection Commission, said in a report that his new agency had hired the core
staff and recruited and trained the required inspectors needed to deploy teams.
