in its support for Palestinian sovereignty in Jerusalem today after a meeting
between President Hosni Mubarak and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat. The
meeting in Alexandria was the sixth time since the collapse of the Camp David
talks last July that the two leaders met. Neither spoke with reporters. ''As
there is Israeli sovereignty over west Jerusalem there should be Palestinian
sovereignty over east Jerusalem. This is the logic of justice ... and of
international agreements,'' Foreign Minister Amr Moussa told reporters.
</P>
