homes across Chicago's far northern and western suburbs for possible
contamination by mercury, a toxic metal that can damage the kidneys and brain.
The first homes inspected will be those where old-fashioned gas regulators have
been removed within the past five years, Nicor Gas said today. Nicor began
looking into possible mercury spills on July 20 when the company discovered
traces from a liquid mercury spill after a contractor replaced an old gas
regulator, which controls the flow of natural gas.
