any additions or subtractions, he's our No. 3 starter. ... SS Alex
Gonzalez, on the DL since July 28 with a sprained knee, will be
recalled Friday. RHP Brad Penny and Chris Clapinski will be
recalled Saturday and Monday, respectfully.
Diamondbacks-Expos:
</P>
<P>
   ARIZONA: 3B Matt Williams, 1-for-20 on the road trip, didn't
start. Craig Counsell started at third base. ... The Expos are the
only team that Randy Johnson has faced and yet to win against.
Johnson is 0-2 in four career starts against Montreal. Johnson, who
made his major league debut with Montreal in 1988, has never
pitched against the Diamondbacks.
</P>
<P>
   MONTREAL: The Expos lineup featured five switch-hitters, the
third time Montreal has had that many switch-hitters in their
batting order this season. The Expos, who also had five
switch-hitters face Johnson on Aug. 9, had switch-hitters Wilton
Guerrero batting leadoff, Milton Bradley batting second, Jose Vidro
hitting third, Geoff Blum in the fifth spot and Fernando Seguignol
batting sixth.
Giants-Pirates:
</P>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO: The Giants' trip to Philadelphia and Pittsburgh
represents the third time this month they've crossed the country.
Adding to the challenge is a flu bug that's attacked the team. ''I
think about half the people in here are on medication,'' manager
Dusty Baker said. ... After two consecutive shutouts, Livan
Hernandez was pounded for seven hits in two innings by the Pirates
on Tuesday. Said C Bobby Estalella, ''He didn't have the stuff he
normally has and he got behind in the count a lot. He just hasn't
been hit like that -- not since spring training.'' ... Reliever Alan
Embree has been a second-half star for the Giants. Entering
Wednesday's game he was on a streak of 12 consecutive scoreless
appearances and had stranded 18 of the 19 runners he'd inherited in
that span. ''He's been awesome,'' Baker said. ''He's always been a
good second-half pitcher.''
</P>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH: Kris Benson was lifted after eight innings Tuesday
even though he was working on a one-hitter. Benson had just been
given extra rest between starts because of a tired arm and had
thrown 119 pitches in the game. To manager Gene Lamont, the move
was perfectly logical so he became upset when he was asked on
Wednesday if he thought about letting Benson finish. ''That's a
dumb question,'' Lamont said. ''If you ask that question, you don't
know anything about our team and what's been going on. If you ask
that question, you either don't know anything about baseball or
you're dumb.'' ... Kevin Young pulled a groin muscle Monday and
hasn't played since then. If the Sept. 1 roster expansion weren't
coming up this week, Young might be on the DL. The Pirates have
been using John Vander Wal at first base.
