<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-30 23:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ill. Man Indicted of Asian Atacks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- A grand jury has indicted a man suspected of
attacking several Asian women in Chicago suburbs.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Anthony Lewis, 33, of Chicago was in Cook County Circuit
Court on Wednesday as the indictments were read. He faces 212
counts, including rape, aggravated criminal sexual assault,
kidnapping, and hate crimes.
</P>
<P>
   If convicted on at least two counts of aggravated criminal
sexual assault, he could be eligible for life in prison, said Mark
Cavins, chief of the sex crimes division at the state attorney's
office.
</P>
<P>
   Cavins said 10 women were attacked between April and July by an
attacker who posed as a census taker, an FBI agent, an immigration
official or a police officer to get into women's homes.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis was arrested in the Philippines last month and is being
held without bail. He has denied involvement in the attacks.
</P>
<P>
   His attorney, Robert Sharp, could not be reached for comment
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities have said DNA analysis linked Lewis to three victims
and his car matches the description of one seen at the scene of an
attack.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
