<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-30 23:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Doctors Accused of Murder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) -- Thai police Wednesday accused two
doctors and a former hospital executive of killing two patients in
order to harvest their kidneys for sale to other patients who
wanted transplants.
</P>
<P>
   Police charged the three with conspiring to commit murder and
accused them of transplanting kidneys illegally from dead patients,
according to a report submitted to the state prosecutor's office.
</P>
<P>
   It's not clear how the patients died.
</P>
<P>
   The state attorney will decide soon whether to prosecute them,
said Anuchart Kongmalai, a state attorney.
</P>
<P>
   Sirot Karnjanaprasertpol, the former director of Vachiraprakarn
Hospital, another doctor and the hospital manager were charged with
conspiracy to commit murder and falsifying documents certifying the
deaths of the two patients. They have already denied the
allegations.
</P>
<P>
   They deny the allegations.
</P>
<P>
   Police dropped the charges against a fourth suspect whom they
plan to use as a witness.
</P>
<P>
   The alleged offenses came to light last year, after a relative
of one of the victims took his story to the media.
</P>
<P>
   Previously published information on the case indicated that the
hospital officials were not accused of actively causing the
victims' deaths, but rather cutting corners in declaring a patient
legally dead.
</P>
<P>
   The case started in February, when Thailand's Medical Council --
a medical ethics board -- revoked or suspended the medical licenses
of several doctors at the hospital after finding they had illegally
traded in human organs.
</P>
<P>
   The council said it had sufficient evidence to show doctors had
procured kidneys.
</P>
<P>
   Trading in organs is prohibited in Thailand. Organ donation is
supposed to be done by agreement between donors and recipients with
no money changing hands.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-30-00 2357 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
